The paper discusses the development of a theory for dealing with uncertain and conflicting sources of information, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Specifically, the focus on artificial reasoning suggests that cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the combination of information, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The use of mathematical foundations and rules of combination suggests that cs.IT is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on the efficiency and generality of the approach suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (social and information networks).
